Argentina complete the top five on 37 goals, the vast majority of which have arrived from Manchester City's main man Sergio Aguero (17 goals).

Senegal (35 goals), Scotland (28) and Ivory Coast (22) come next on the list, with Holland (19), Brazil (18), the Republic of Ireland (18) and Chile (17) - helped by the goalscoring form of Alexis Sanchez - further down.

Players from 46 countries have found the back of the net this season, with a total of 800 goals scored so far.

 

